For sale is this Cold Woodsman chambered in .22lr. Low speed housing so this gun would need low velocity .22 rounds to avoid excessive spring wear. The bluing on the gun overall is intact with wear on the barreland minor edge wear. 

Internals are clean and the bore and rifling is sharp, no mechanical problems at all and the gun functions beautifully.

This gun has not been altered or reblued, the Colt pony is still visible, usually a good sign the gun is in original unfinished condition.

title: For Sale:  2 840rd Cans of Lake City M196 Tracer Rounds On 10rd Stripper Clips
postcontent: 2 840rd Cans of Lake City M196 Tracer Rounds on 10rd Stripper Clips. Great for night shoots, and for showing you when your mag is empty. A common misconception with tracer rounds is that they scratch/damage the barrel more than your average range ammo. This is simply not true. The reason tracers light up is because of a solid chemical compound at the base of the round that is lit by the ignition of the powder in the brass. The "tracer" part never actually touches the barrel. One of the cans was opened, and some of the rounds taken out of the clips, but all were returned to the stripper clips. The stripper clips come in 120rd bandoliers inside each can. They also come with metal followers, which allow you to quickly load magazines, both PMAGs and G.I. mags. Each can costs $650 dollars, and comes with an unused, N.I.B. 30rd G.I. mag. $1200 for both cans, with the G.I. mags. Please no low ball offers. title: For Sale:  Remington 700 7mm magnum 2 stocks stainless barrel
postcontent:
For bidding, please see Gunbroker listing at:
http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=333568467


For sale is a Remington Model 700, 100% stainless steel barrel, bolt-action, 7mm Remington magnum rifle with BOTH a synthetic stock AND a walnut wood stock.  
This is a firearm that can give you the best of both worlds when choosing the best hunting gun for your taste.  You don‚Äôt have to choose between the modern look and ruggedness of a synthetic stock and the quality feel and finish of the recently refinished walnut wood stock.  Both stocks are included in this auction and can be switched very quickly.
Great time went in to refinishing the walnut stock for this gun.  A careful selection and treatment of oil and finish have made it ready to stand up to the elements, while still showing a beautiful flame pattern and still retaining that well used look.  The walnut stock basically looks like Grandpa‚Äôs old faithful gun that he has used for years, but restored so that it is ready for another lifetime of weather.  Very much like what Fender does with their 50‚Äôs and 60‚Äôs reissue guitars giving them the worn look but they are going to hold up like they are new.   Both stocks have the raised cheekpiece and a recoil pad.
The stainless steel barrel was recently polished along with the bolt and shows no blemishes.  This barrel will last forever.  The inside of the barrel is clean, and in great shape having been scrubbed down as a part of the refinish process.  Barrel is drilled and filled with stainless screws to add open sights if you wanted.  Receiver is drilled and tapped for two piece weaver scope mounts(which are included).  There is a recessed muzzle crown without any blemishes.
Action is smooth as you would expect from a 700, reliable feeding.  Trigger is a crisp break consistently at 5 pounds.
The 7mm Rem Mag cartridge was developed and introduced along with the introduction of the Remington 700 bolt action rifle.  This is a great pairing to have these two together.  So much in fact that when Remington introduced their 50th anniversary 700 edition, it was in 7mm Rem Mag.  The 7mm Remington Magnum offers ballistics better than the .30-06 Springfield with bullet weights of 160 grains and less, due both to the higher muzzle velocity of the magnum compared to the Springfield and that .284 diameter bullets tend to have better ballistic coefficients than .308 diameter bullets of comparable mass.  However, the 7 mm Rem Mag can be loaded with bullets up to 220 grains.  The 7mm rem mag is about a flat a shooter as you are going to get without going to something like a 338 Lapua or 50 BMG.

title: For Sale:  Kel Tec P11 compact 9mm
postcontent:
This is an excellent carry pistol. Comes with the box, a magazine with mag extension & a holster. It weighs 14 oz. unloaded and 20 oz with loaded magazine. It also has, glow in the dark, night sights.
The P-11 is a semi-automatic, locked-breech, DAO, pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. Ten round and optional twelve round magazines available. The Kel- Tec P-11 is compact and lightweight, thanks to its locked breech. Its ergonometry, perceived recoil and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-11 is especially well suited for plain-clothes police officers, security personnel, or as a secondary weapon for military service members. 
The P-11 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, frame, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 Ordnance steel heat treated to 47 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer and operates in Double Action Only. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. The functioning of the mechanism surpasses all applicable SAAMI safety standards. The grip is made of the ultra high impact polymer DuPont ST-8018. The grip also forms the magazine well and the trigger guard. Normally supplied with a 10-round double column all steel magazine.
